main event: A bright, light-colored object with a dome on top and glowing base was observed high in the sky, moving rapidly in a northwest direction. It was observed for about 20 minutes before disappearing in the distance.
interesting points: The object did not appear to have any propulsion system and the witness stated they had never seen anything like it before.
The object seemed to have a dome on top and a glowing base, and moved rather rapidly.
The witness observed the object for about 20 minutes before it disappeared from view in the distance.
Other similar sightings of bright, unidentified objects were reported in the area.
The object did not make any sound and the witness was unable to identify it as any known type of aircraft.
sighted object: a bright, light-colored object with a dome on top and glowing base
witnesses: one witness, a control tower operator at Norton AFB
